  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Victims of Disasters Receive Extended After Care</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The outpouring of generosity often benefits victims of natural disaster in the immediate aftermath of the horrendous trauma. Often victims are left alone to discover their post-disaster normalcy. In their vulnerability, victims are often preyed upon by human traffickers. GRACE provides awareness, counseling services and financial assistance through the next weeks, months and year. Provisions are customized to their needs and may include funds for groceries, clothing, furniture, and housing.</narrative>
  </description>
